instructions: Be ready to stack/organize clothes, shout at passersby to let people know what's going on, chat up the customers to increase sales (everything's free), and find some cool picks for yourself (just don't take everything)
Please see the detailed instructions on the planning document!
For setup, we just need to set out some snack and make sure the movie is playing. Otherwise, just show up and enjoy the film!

For setup, tables will need to be arranged, signs drawn on the chalkboards and posted around the union, and vendors welcomed! After that, just help pass out knick-knacks, table for GW, and keep our vendors happy and occupado!
Wear your coolest fitness gear (shin guard and a helmet never hurt). Also pls wear shoes that don't leave scuff marks.

1st, Meet up in a group around 10 am at Reaves park (exact location in park will be communicated on slack). Pick up materials from Michele (gloves, trashbags, and trash grabbers)
2nd, Pass out materials to volunteers by 10:15
3rd, Scout out which areas of the park need the most clean-up. We can either split up into groups or all head to the same areas depending on the amount of people.
4th, Dispose of trash bags properly (either through Michele, Matthew, or local dumpster)

1st, one volunteer heads to Midway Deli around 10:30 to pick up food and snacks. Finish up Trash pick-up around 10:50.
2nd, set up food on benches and/or picnic blankets (bring your own!).
3rd, have a quick meal before the bike ride!! :)
Be ready to schmoove around Norman on your bike. Matt's gonna bring water and some tools just in case, and Gracie will be leading our ride.
